%% Diagram: TAO read and write paths
%% Type: sequence
%%{init: {'htmlLabels': false}}%%
sequenceDiagram
    autonumber
    participant Client
    participant F as Follower (slave region)
    participant LB as Leader (slave region)
    participant LA as Leader (master region)
    participant DB as MySQL master

    Note over Client,DB: Read — cache hit
    Client->>F: assoc_range(id1, atype, 0, 50)
    F-->>Client: cached prefix

    Note over Client,DB: Read — cache miss
    Client->>F: assoc_get(id1, atype, id2)
    F->>LB: forward miss
    LB->>DB: SELECT (via local slave DB if present)
    DB-->>LB: row(s)
    LB-->>F: data + version
    F-->>Client: data

    Note over Client,DB: Write (slave region)
    Client->>F: assoc_add(id1, atype, id2, time, data)
    F->>LB: forward write
    LB->>LA: cross-region forward to master leader
    LA->>DB: INSERT (synchronous write-through)
    DB-->>LA: ack
    LA-->>LB: changeset (incl. inverse for id2's shard)
    LB-->>F: changeset (read-after-write within tier)
    F-->>Client: ack
    LA--)LB: async invalidate/refill via replication stream
    LB--)F: async invalidate/refill (other followers in tier)
